import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna(subset=['income', 'region'])
    chart = sns.boxplot(x='region', y='income', data=data)
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, horizontalalignment='right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income across different regions?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='population', ascending=False)
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    sns.barplot(x='country', y='population', data=data, palette='Blues_d')
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the population distribution across different countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
